Principal Deputy National Security Advisor Jon Finer participated in a virtual roundtable with LGBTQI+ human rights activists as part of the White House's celebration of Pride Month. Finer emphasized the Biden-Harris Administration's commitment to protecting LGBTQI+ human rights globally, in line with President Biden's Memorandum on this issue and Executive Order on Advancing Equality for LGBTQI+ Individuals. Activists highlighted the resilience of the LGBTQI+ community in the face of gains and repression, as well as ongoing discrimination, violence, and criminalization. They also expressed concerns about increasing online attacks and state surveillance. Other participants included U.S. Special Envoy Jessica Stern, USAID Senior Coordinator Jay Gilliam, and senior members of the National Security Council staff.